description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directorate Support Manager (Band 7)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our dedicated, enthusiastic and fun loving Urgent Care Division is seeking a new team member&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an essential role in the team, working closely with clinicians across the wide spectrum of Urgent care supporting the delivery of timely care for patients. You will be instrumental in the delivery of systems and processes to improve timely access to care at the Front Door. Your highly developed people skills will enable you to build relationships, advocating partnership working, thus contributing to an improved patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are at the beginning of several large projects, including the future design of our urgent care services. This is a great opportunity to enhance your operational skills and to really work at the heart of urgent care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to say that it really is an exciting time to join Worcestershire Acute Hospitals and this is a role that offers an enthusiastic and ambitious individual hands on experience of Urgent Care Management and an opportunity to be involved in our organisations continuing journey of improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to receiving your application, please do not hesitate to contact us for any questions you may regarding the role or to know more about our organisation&lt;/p&gt;
